<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      Ledge distribution entitlements (Developer ID + Hardened Runtime). See issue #194.

      Policy:
        - App Sandbox stays DISABLED (CGEventTap touch remapper + USB HID need it off).
          The absence of com.apple.security.app-sandbox = sandbox off. Do NOT add it.
        - Keep this MINIMAL. Do NOT add com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
          or com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory: there are no
          third-party frameworks bundled, so neither is needed, and both broadly weaken
          a non-sandboxed app that holds Accessibility.
        - CGEventTap (TouchRemapper) and IOHIDManager are TCC-gated (Accessibility /
          Input Monitoring), NOT entitlement-gated - no key here covers them.
        - Each Hardened Runtime resource entitlement below maps to a capability the app
          declares an Info.plist usage string for. If the first functional test of the
          notarised build shows the app never exercises one of these, prune it.
    -->

    <!-- Required: the app drives Chrome (Google Meet) and Spotify via NSAppleScript /
         Apple Events (AppleScriptQueue, GoogleMeetBridge, SpotifyBridge). Without this,
         scripting other apps is blocked under the Hardened Runtime.
         Backed by NSAppleEventsUsageDescription in Info.plist. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.automation.apple-events</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Calendar access. Backed by NSCalendarsFullAccessUsageDescription. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.personal-information.calendars</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Location access. Backed by NSLocationWhenInUseUsageDescription. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.personal-information.location</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Camera access. Backed by NSCameraUsageDescription. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.device.camera</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
